      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "The wind slabs must be evaluated with care and prudence. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular at the base of rock walls and adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. As a consequence of warming during the day and the solar radiation, the likelihood of moist avalanches being released will increase gradually in particular on sunny slopes. <br/> Backcountry touring calls for experience in the assessment of avalanche danger and careful route selection.",
        "highlights": "At elevated altitudes a considerable avalanche danger will still be encountered."
